column5: Big box for sure. Fifteen pounds of perch filets is a big bag also eh? The first two fish are the same fish...musta mixed up the pictures.

Look again Roy ..lol. the fish should be differant unless i did make a miss take in posting them , 15 pounds of perch filets is my PB . We have more pic's to show if this old computer will stay running .....lol.
The proof is in the fish dish........lol
A great catch there Skipper. But yes, the first two are the same fish. Congrats.
Nice catch, but they don't look like fillets to me.  I was wondering how many perch fillets it would take to make 15lbs. I know its a lot more than 100 perch worth!!  S.

Not when they are JUMBO Lake Erie perch...the perch we caught yesterday on Erie we long, fat and WIDE bodied....they are getting huge eating gobies....but if caught in the spring time, they are weigh even more but the fillets are THIN as most of their energy goes into the eggs.
Think I see some bass tails there?  Too many bones for this guy.  TFS Skip.
they look like good size perch you were into  nice fishing report
We had 83 in all when finishing the day , proably put that many back .
Thanks  Terry .... might try to show the filets if i can keep this old computer running .....
Good to hear the day went so well for you guys Skipper.  Can't beat a day on the water with your brother !!
I'll often just leave them whole. Carefully placed blade will take all the meat off leaving all the bones intact. Either way, some great meals.
That i would like to learn Roy , after cleaning and skinning we place them in the fridge for and hour or so before doing fillets, makes for easy cutting that way when the meat is firm .
Decent meal there skip..  Back at er again tomorrow I take it?
Thats right Lew , i did feel good to have him with me out there , also gave me the chance to take care of his fifith birthday blue's this week end as well .....lol.
Pepsi?  LOL  Now theres a plate of fish I can chow down on.
Yes there N.A.W. ... we plan to go out again early tomorrow morning .
I mention  its my brothers fifth birthday today , heres a pic of what i bought him , it should keep him pacified when the fish are'nt biting ... right ...lol.
I hate to say it but that's one ugly kindergarten kid...
Heres what you get when you cross a Townsend fish skinner with a electric can opener and a sewing machine foot peddle....We thank La La for this one .

Bouy the sun rise took its time this morning , so much for early any more . Guess we're going to make the best of it and get on the water in the next few minutes , if any one needs to find us we'll be in between a couple of islands doing the Perching thing . Good luck to every one else out there today .

The day is here , the first of four . My self Skipper and Baby La La my brother from eastern Ontario are just about ready to head it out on the lake and get some fishing in . Hopefuly later  today we can come back with a report of how the day went and have some pictures to show , also  the 2'x4' tackle box has arrived filled with fishing goodies which i hope to give every one a look at ..lol.. , Wish us luck , were off .
Have a great day Skipper, looks like you've got the weather for it
tite lines Skipper dude  lets see what you can do
Good Luck ! We want fish porn.
..so in other words you still don't have anything to report  go get em
Can't wait to see the pics! Good luck! Enjoy the sunshine!
Kemp was list glass this morning, with a few boats our perchin.  Looks like a nice fall day on the water.  Good luck, and don't forget the camera
so you are reporting that you will at sometime have a report
I came for the pics. There are none. I AM DISAPPOINT.
There is a spot to post your status on the main page
Remember. Pics or it didn't happen.
First was the pre-pre-report. Now we have the pre-report.  Still gets more hits than my actual report... Maybe he's onto something
yeah I feel the same way....
Waiting for the report! I am fish vicariously thru you this weekend, dont let me down! LOL
Don't forget the post between pre report, and pre pre report.  The plea for help to save the stranded fisherman near bellville.  The little bruder i'm assuming..
Welcome to face book! HH
headhunter thats one hilarious quote haha
I was going to look at the detailed election results but I'm just consumed at the thought of our 14% revenue drop because skip hasn't posted in 22 hours.
LOL

Skipper,  All fishermen are liars, except you and me....and I have my doubts about you.....  PICTURES or BUST......  BTW I soon be leaving for some Lake Erie Perch action...but there will be NO pictures because they all look a like after awhile....
Hey Roy, giv'em a break. They were still working on loading the 2'X4' tackle box back on the truck..........
Im sorry but there seems to be an intelligence issue preventing translation, it's on your end btw.

God ohope i can post this for the fourth time , computer is freezing up on me , might have to wait till my note book comes back to do this , ok i'll try giving a bit of fish porn before ther stupid thing shuts down again
first pic is of LaLa's tackle box , just fits the truck .lol...... , other pics are a few of the prrch we caughtt , 15 pounds of filets when we were done ....
